# LoadZone Next App

- Use App Router conventions and prefer React Server Components by default.
- Add `'use client'` only for real interactivity, browser APIs, or local UI state.
- Read page data directly in server components with Prisma or server helpers.
- Use Server Actions for mutations in `apps/app` and `apps/player`.
- Use API routes only when they are actually needed:
  public player endpoints, webhooks, chat, push, or external integrations.
- Keep admin auth checks in server layouts/pages with Clerk-backed helpers.
- Keep player token validation in the player shell, middleware, or server entry points.
- Use route-level `loading.tsx` / `error.tsx` when a route needs explicit loading or failure UX.
